# dogfood-lifecycle-pack ontology — session-lifecycle vocabulary for
# Operation Dogfood (v26.7.13). Models a Claude Code session's tool events
# (Bash / Edit / Write / Read / Task / ...) as PROV-O provenance so that a
# session log (one Turtle node appended per tool event by a PostToolUse
# hook) can be validated by `ggen graph validate --files <session.ttl>
# --shapes shapes.ttl`.
#
# PUBLIC-ONTOLOGY-FIRST (same doctrine as packs/soc2-audit-pack/ontology.ttl
# and packs/dry-run-publish-pack/pack.toml): every relationship that a public
# vocabulary already covers reuses that vocabulary; a private namespace (dfl:)
# is minted ONLY for terms with no public equivalent, and each such term
# carries an rdfs:comment naming the public ontologies checked and why they
# do not fit.
#
# Public vocabularies used (NOT redefined here — used by IRI):
#   prov:    A SESSION is a prov:Activity (dfl:Session subclass, below); each
#            TOOL EVENT is a prov:Activity (dfl:ToolEvent subclass); the
#            operator and each subagent are prov:Agent. Reused predicates:
#              prov:wasAssociatedWith  tool event -> the agent that ran it
#              prov:actedOnBehalfOf    subagent   -> the session's agent
#              prov:used               tool event -> its input entity
#              prov:generated          tool event -> its result entity
#            Tool inputs/outputs are prov:Entity nodes named by the repo's
#            existing content-address scheme urn:blake3:<hex> (crates/
#            chatman-common provenance::content_address; crates/cng
#            pipeline.rs ImportedArtifact.source_iri).
#   dcterms: dcterms:identifier  the session id (opaque session/uuid string)
#            dcterms:isPartOf     tool event -> the session it belongs to
#                                 (the "session ref"; PROV core has no
#                                 sub-activity predicate, so the public DCMI
#                                 part/whole relation carries it)
#            dcterms:description  human-readable notes on any node
#   skos:    skos:ConceptScheme + skos:Concept + skos:notation + skos:inScheme
#            model the two closed vocabularies (tool names, outcomes) exactly
#            as packs/soc2-audit-pack models the AICPA TSC taxonomy — SKOS
#            concepts, not a minted class hierarchy. skos:notation is also the
#            deterministic string handle carried directly on a tool-event node
#            (its tool name), matching soc2-shapes.ttl.tmpl's use of
#            skos:notation as a handle on prov:Activity nodes.
#   time:    time:inXSDDateTimeStamp  the event's timestamp (an OWL-Time
#            xsd:dateTimeStamp literal — a graph-carried time value, never a
#            wall-clock read; see CLAUDE.md invariant 3).
#
@prefix dfl:     <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/dogfood-lifecycle#> .
@prefix prov:    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix skos:    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix time:    <http://www.w3.org/2006/time#> .
@prefix rdf:     <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:     <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# ── Obligation-derivation extension (v26.7.18) ─────────────────────────────
# Adds a minimal but real derived-obligation vocabulary so hook.ttl (sibling
# file, same directory) can CONSTRUCT a parameterized dfl:Obligation from a
# dfl:Blocked dfl:ToolEvent via praxis-graphlaw's real `kh:`
# TripleStore::load_hook_pack + .materialize() mechanism — the SAME engine
# packs/self-monitoring-pack/hook.ttl already uses in production-shaped form
# (see that file's own header), not a hand-simulated derivation. Verified by
# a scratch consumer crate (see this pack's README "Obligation derivation —
# verified" section) since this pack ships no templates/no ggen.toml wiring
# of its own to route it through.
#
# DISCLOSED MINTED TERMS (this extension, capability-justified):
#   dfl:Obligation  a node CONSTRUCTed when a dfl:ToolEvent's dfl:outcome is
#     dfl:Blocked. Checked prov: (no Obligation/duty concept — prov:Activity
#     models what happened, not what is owed), W3C ODRL (models rights/duties
#     for licensing/policy exchange, far heavier than a single derived
#     review-duty node and pulls in an unrelated commercial-rights vocab).
#     No public equivalent at this weight; mirrors packs/self-monitoring-
#     pack's smon:EscalationObligation pattern (derived-fact node from a
#     CONSTRUCT hook).
#   dfl:derivedFrom  Obligation -> the dfl:ToolEvent that triggered it
#     (parameter: which fact). No public equivalent found (prov:wasDerivedFrom
#     is Entity-to-Entity, not Activity-to-Obligation).
#   dfl:obligationTarget  Obligation -> the prov:Agent responsible for
#     discharging it (parameter: target). Reuses prov:Agent as range; the
#     property itself is minted since PROV has no "owes a duty to" predicate.
#   dfl:severity + dfl:Severity  Obligation -> one of a closed 3-concept SKOS
#     scheme (dfl:High/dfl:Medium/dfl:Low) (parameter: severity). Mirrors the
#     dfl:Outcome closed-scheme pattern above.
#   dfl:deadline  Obligation -> an xsd:duration literal, e.g. "PT24H"
#     (parameter: deadline). A duration, not a computed timestamp, so no term
#     here is a wall-clock read (CLAUDE.md invariant 3) — it is a POLICY
#     CONSTANT the CONSTRUCT template emits verbatim, not `now() + 24h`.
#   dfl:obligationStatus + dfl:ObligationStatus  Obligation -> one of a
#     closed 3-concept SKOS scheme (dfl:Open/dfl:Discharged/dfl:Refused).
#     dfl:Open is what derive_review_obligation.ttl's CONSTRUCT asserts;
#     dfl:Discharged/dfl:Refused are asserted by the companion
#     discharge_review_obligation.ttl hook (lifecycle tracking, not merely
#     emission — see hooks/README note below).
#   dfl:dischargedBy  Obligation -> the dfl:ToolEvent whose later dfl:Ok
#     outcome, from the same prov:Agent in the same dfl:Session, discharges
#     it. Existence of this triple is what makes an obligation queryable as
#     closed vs still-open.
#   dfl:firesAfter  a pack-level (not hook-level) rdf:Property asserting this
#     pack's derivation should be scheduled after another named hook pack's
#     derivation when co-loaded over one union graph — the COMPOSABILITY
#     declaration this pack makes in RDF (see the assertion below and
#     hook.ttl's real kh:after, which is what praxis-graphlaw's
#     `hooks::schedule_hooks` Kahn's-algorithm topological sort actually
#     reads; dfl:firesAfter is the human-readable RDF-level disclosure of
#     that same fact, kept in step with hook.ttl's kh:after value by hand).
#     No public vocabulary expresses hook-execution precedence.

dfl:Obligation
    a               rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label      "Obligation" ;
    rdfs:comment    "A derived duty to review a dfl:Blocked tool event, CONSTRUCTed by hook.ttl's derive_review_obligation hook. Carries dfl:derivedFrom (which event), dfl:obligationTarget (who), dfl:severity, dfl:deadline (all parameters usable by a downstream planner), and dfl:obligationStatus (lifecycle state)." .

dfl:derivedFrom
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "derivedFrom" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:ToolEvent ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a derived Obligation back to the ToolEvent fact that triggered its derivation." .

dfl:obligationTarget
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "obligationTarget" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  prov:Agent ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a derived Obligation to the agent responsible for discharging it." .

dfl:deadline
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "deadline" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:duration ;
    rdfs:comment "A policy-constant duration (e.g. \"PT24H\"^^xsd:duration) within which the obligation should be discharged, emitted verbatim by the CONSTRUCT template -- never a computed wall-clock timestamp." .

dfl:dischargedBy
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "dischargedBy" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:ToolEvent ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a discharged Obligation to the later dfl:Ok ToolEvent (same agent, same session) that discharged it. Asserted by hook.ttl's discharge_review_obligation hook, never by derive_review_obligation." .

# ── Escalation extension (v26.7.19, Obligation-lifecycle L3->L4) ───────────
# dfl:escalatedBy follows the SAME "optional pointer property, not a status
# enum value" discipline as dfl:dischargedBy (see hook.ttl's own note on why
# obligationStatus cannot safely carry a third append-only value): an
# Obligation that has gone 3+ later same-agent/same-session ToolEvents
# without being discharged is OVERDUE, and hook.ttl's third hook
# (escalate_overdue_obligation) CONSTRUCTs dfl:escalatedBy pointing at the
# ToolEvent whose sequenceIndex crossed that threshold. Deliberately NOT
# gated on "not yet discharged" (no FILTER NOT EXISTS -- see hook.ttl's own
# documented parse failure with that construct): both dfl:escalatedBy and
# dfl:dischargedBy may legitimately coexist on the same Obligation (it
# escalated for being slow, then was later discharged anyway) -- this is
# truthful append-only history, not a contradiction, and is why escalation
# is its own pointer property rather than a mutually-exclusive
# obligationStatus value that would violate shapes.ttl's existing
# sh:maxCount 1 on that property.
dfl:escalatedBy
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "escalatedBy" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:ToolEvent ;
    rdfs:comment "Links an overdue Obligation to the later same-agent/same-session ToolEvent whose sequenceIndex first crossed the escalation threshold (derivedFrom's sequenceIndex + 3), asserted by hook.ttl's escalate_overdue_obligation hook. May coexist with dfl:dischargedBy (escalated-then-discharged is truthful history, not a contradiction)." .

dfl:firesAfter
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "firesAfter" ;
    rdfs:comment "Pack-level RDF disclosure that this pack's hook.ttl derivation is scheduled after another named hook pack's derivation when both are co-loaded over one union graph via praxis-graphlaw's kh:after + hooks::schedule_hooks topological sort. Kept in step by hand with hook.ttl's actual kh:after triple." .

<http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/dogfood-lifecycle>
    dfl:firesAfter <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/self-monitoring> ;
    rdfs:comment   "Declares dogfood-lifecycle-pack's derive_review_obligation hook fires after self-monitoring-pack's derive_escalation_obligation hook when both packs' hook.ttl + ontology.ttl are co-loaded into one praxis-graphlaw TripleStore -- see hook.ttl's kh:after triple, which is the fact praxis-graphlaw's scheduler actually reads." .

dfl:Severity
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Severity" ;
    rdfs:comment "Closed 3-concept SKOS scheme of Obligation severities. Exactly three individuals exist (dfl:High, dfl:Medium, dfl:Low)." .

dfl:SeverityScheme
    a            skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label   "Obligation severity scheme" .

dfl:High   a dfl:Severity , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:SeverityScheme ; skos:notation "high" ; skos:prefLabel "high" .
dfl:Medium a dfl:Severity , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:SeverityScheme ; skos:notation "medium" ; skos:prefLabel "medium" .
dfl:Low    a dfl:Severity , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:SeverityScheme ; skos:notation "low" ; skos:prefLabel "low" .

dfl:obligationStatus
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "obligationStatus" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:ObligationStatus ;
    rdfs:comment "Links an Obligation to its lifecycle state (dfl:Open / dfl:Discharged / dfl:Refused)." .

dfl:severity
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "severity" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:Severity ;
    rdfs:comment "Links an Obligation to its severity concept." .

dfl:ObligationStatus
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "ObligationStatus" ;
    rdfs:comment "Closed 3-concept SKOS scheme of Obligation lifecycle states. Exactly three individuals exist (dfl:Open, dfl:Discharged, dfl:Refused)." .

dfl:ObligationStatusScheme
    a            skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label   "Obligation status scheme" .

dfl:Open       a dfl:ObligationStatus , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ObligationStatusScheme ; skos:notation "open" ; skos:prefLabel "open" .
dfl:Discharged a dfl:ObligationStatus , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ObligationStatusScheme ; skos:notation "discharged" ; skos:prefLabel "discharged" .
dfl:Refused    a dfl:ObligationStatus , skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ObligationStatusScheme ; skos:notation "refused" ; skos:prefLabel "refused" .

# DISCLOSED MINTED TERMS (dfl:, capability-justified — no public equivalent):
#   dfl:Session, dfl:ToolEvent  rdfs:subClassOf prov:Activity. PROV models
#     both a whole session and a single tool invocation as bare prov:Activity
#     with no subtype to tell them apart; SHACL needs a precise sh:targetClass
#     so the tool-event shape can require a tool name / sequence / outcome
#     WITHOUT imposing those on the session node. Checked prov: (no such
#     subtype) and schema.org Action (models a completed action but not the
#     session/step distinction, and pulls in an unrelated commercial vocab).
#   dfl:sequenceIndex  monotonic per-session ordinal (xsd:integer). PROV has
#     no event ordinal; OLO (olo:index) supplies one but only as a slot in a
#     fully materialized olo:OrderedList, which is far heavier than a hook
#     emitting an incrementing counter. Minted as a plain datatype property.
#   dfl:outcome + dfl:Outcome  a tool event's terminal status drawn from the
#     CLOSED 3-value vocabulary {ok, error, blocked}. No public ontology
#     enumerates tool-invocation outcomes; this mirrors packs/jira-tracking-
#     pack's closed jira:Status scheme (jira:status -> jira:Alive et al.).
#     dcterms:type was checked and rejected: it names a resource's genre, not
#     a process step's observed result.
#
# OBSERVATION-ONLY FENCE: this vocabulary describes what a tool event
# OBSERVABLY did; it never asserts authority, permission, or actuation. No
# term here is named authorize / permit / grant / actuate / execute. The
# outcome vocabulary records ok / error / blocked as observations, never a
# grant of permission — admission, hooks, and receipts are separate governed
# surfaces (crates/praxis-graphlaw/src/chatman).

# ── Classes (minted subclasses of prov:Activity — disclosed above) ────────

dfl:Session
    a               rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf prov:Activity ;
    rdfs:label      "Session" ;
    rdfs:comment    "One Claude Code session, as a prov:Activity. Carries dcterms:identifier (the opaque session/uuid) and prov:wasAssociatedWith its acting agent. Minted subtype of prov:Activity so the SHACL tool-event shape can target dfl:ToolEvent without also constraining the session node." .

dfl:ToolEvent
    a               rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf prov:Activity ;
    rdfs:label      "ToolEvent" ;
    rdfs:comment    "One tool invocation within a session (Bash / Edit / Write / Read / Task / ...), as a prov:Activity. Required attributes are enforced by shapes.ttl: dcterms:isPartOf (session ref), skos:notation (tool name), dfl:sequenceIndex OR time:inXSDDateTimeStamp (ordering), dfl:outcome (closed status), plus prov:wasAssociatedWith / prov:used / prov:generated." .

dfl:Outcome
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Outcome" ;
    rdfs:comment "The closed class of tool-event terminal statuses. Exactly three individuals exist (dfl:Ok, dfl:Error, dfl:Blocked); do not add more without updating shapes.ttl's sh:in list in the same edit. Mirrors packs/jira-tracking-pack's closed jira:Status. Observation only — records what a tool event did, never that it was permitted to." .

# ── Minted properties (disclosed above) ───────────────────────────────────

dfl:sequenceIndex
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "sequenceIndex" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:ToolEvent ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:integer ;
    rdfs:comment "Monotonic per-session ordinal of this tool event (0-based or 1-based; strictly increasing within one session). No public ontology offers a lightweight event ordinal — OLO's olo:index requires a materialized ordered list. A hook emits an incrementing counter." .

dfl:outcome
    a           rdf:Property ;
    rdfs:label  "outcome" ;
    rdfs:domain dfl:ToolEvent ;
    rdfs:range  dfl:Outcome ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a tool event to its terminal outcome individual (dfl:Ok / dfl:Error / dfl:Blocked). Mirrors jira:status. Observation of the tool's observed result, never a permission grant." .

# ── Closed outcome vocabulary (SKOS; observation only) ────────────────────

dfl:OutcomeScheme
    a            skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label   "Tool-event outcome scheme" ;
    rdfs:comment "Closed 3-concept scheme of tool-event terminal outcomes." .

dfl:Ok
    a            dfl:Outcome , skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme dfl:OutcomeScheme ;
    skos:notation "ok" ;
    skos:prefLabel "ok" ;
    rdfs:comment  "The tool ran and returned a normal result." .

dfl:Error
    a            dfl:Outcome , skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme dfl:OutcomeScheme ;
    skos:notation "error" ;
    skos:prefLabel "error" ;
    rdfs:comment  "The tool ran and returned an error result (non-zero exit, exception, failed edit)." .

dfl:Blocked
    a            dfl:Outcome , skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme dfl:OutcomeScheme ;
    skos:notation "blocked" ;
    skos:prefLabel "blocked" ;
    rdfs:comment  "The tool invocation was stopped before completion by a governed surface (a hook, the permission system). An OBSERVATION that the call did not run to completion — not a statement about authority." .

# ── Closed tool-name vocabulary (SKOS) ────────────────────────────────────
# A tool event carries skos:notation directly (its tool name, e.g. "Bash").
# These concepts are the authoritative enumeration of valid notations;
# shapes.ttl's sh:in list must be kept in step with this scheme.

dfl:ToolNameScheme
    a            skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label   "Claude Code tool-name scheme" ;
    rdfs:comment "Closed enumeration of the tool names a PostToolUse event may carry as its skos:notation handle." .

dfl:Bash     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Bash" ; skos:prefLabel "Bash" .
dfl:Edit     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Edit" ; skos:prefLabel "Edit" .
dfl:Write    a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Write" ; skos:prefLabel "Write" .
dfl:Read     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Read" ; skos:prefLabel "Read" .
dfl:Grep     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Grep" ; skos:prefLabel "Grep" .
dfl:Glob     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Glob" ; skos:prefLabel "Glob" .
dfl:Task     a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "Task" ; skos:prefLabel "Task" .
dfl:WebFetch  a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "WebFetch" ; skos:prefLabel "WebFetch" .
dfl:WebSearch a skos:Concept ; skos:inScheme dfl:ToolNameScheme ; skos:notation "WebSearch" ; skos:prefLabel "WebSearch" .
